==================================
= PXE boot on the SÃ¶kris net4826 =
==================================

Unzip tftpboot.tgz into /srv/var

  $ sudo mkdir -p /srv/var 
  $ sudo chmod -R /srv/var
  $ tar -zxf tftpboot.tgz
  $ mv tftpboot/* /srv/var

Download dnsmasq 
 
  $ sudo apt-get install dnsmasq

Append the following to /etc/dnsmasq.conf

    ## deactivate DNS
    port=0

    ## listen on specific interface and/or address
    interface=eth0
    listen-address=192.168.1.1
    bind-interfaces

    ## DHCP configuration
    dhcp-range=192.168.1.50,192.168.1.150,12h

    # detect PXE clients
    dhcp-vendorclass=set:pxe,PXEClient

    # MACs we serve (MAC address of target) 
    dhcp-host=00:00:24:C8:55:28 

    # do not send default route and DNS server options
    dhcp-option=option:router
    dhcp-option=option:dns-server

    # ignore request from unknown hosts
    dhcp-ignore=tag:!known

    # and ignore non-PXE booting
    dhcp-ignore=tag:!pxe

    ## TFTP configuration
    enable-tftp
    tftp-root=/srv/tftp
    dhcp-boot=pxelinux.0

Start the DHCP and TFTP servers, add an IP addresss for ethernet interface

  # service network-manager stop
  # ifconfig eth0 192.168.1.254 netmask 255.255.255.0
  # service dnsmasq restart

Boot the board, hit ^P at startup, and type 'boot f0' at the boot monitor. 
Do your stuff, be happy. 

Restore previous networking settings:

  # service dnsmasq stop  
  # service network-manager start

